"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-07-29-a-big-pagan-celebration-olympics-critiqued-for-satanism-in-its-homage-to-greek-mythology\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The2024 Summer Olympicshas only just begun, but not without controversy.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 72, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The long-awaited summer games launched on Friday with an extravagant opening ceremony on the Seine River featuring Paris's most avante-garde fashion, art, politics and music.\", \"from\": 74, \"to\": 248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 179, \"end\": 194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_(rapper)\", \"score\": 0.9999915143094644, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"featuring Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_(rapper)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_(rapper)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the lavish opening ceremony that even featuredCeline Dion's comeback has been met with conservative and right-wing pushback and criticism in the United States and across Europe.\", \"from\": 249, \"to\": 435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 403, \"end\": 416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999991855928462, \"rank\": 8.144078965033481e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over the weekend, figures likeHouse Speaker Mike Johnson(R-La.)\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"andElon Musktook to social media to air out their grievances with the claims of anti-Christian sentiment from the Olympics.\", \"from\": 501, \"to\": 624, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 581, \"end\": 605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anti-Christian_sentiment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"anti-Christian sentiment\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anti-Christian_sentiment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anti-Christian_sentiment\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Conservative Hollywood figures likeCandace Cameron BureandRob\\u00a0Schneideralso joined in on the complaints against the Olympics for one particular vignette in the sprawling four-hour spectacle that traversed Paris, from the sewers to the Louvre.\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 867, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 638, \"end\": 647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.644829018732157e-14, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 830, \"end\": 835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.26274870958922e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 860, \"end\": 866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.999986334332487, \"rank\": 1.3665854109999827e-05, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a reel on Instagram Bure stated, \\\"I love the Olympic Games .\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.585536994390479e-34, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \".\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 934, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \".So to watch such an incredible and wonderful event that's gonna take place over the next two weeks and see the opening ceremonies completely blaspheme and mock the Christian faith with their interpretation of the Last Supper was disgusting .\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 1177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1100, \"end\": 1109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9859751275191647, \"rank\": 0.014224367420219246, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \".\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1179, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \".\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1181, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It made me so sad.\\\"\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Schneider also shared on social media, \\\"I cannot watch an Olympics that disrespects Christianity and openly celebrates Satan.\\\"\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1203, \"end\": 1212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schneider-Creusot\", \"score\": 0.9992209032576808, \"rank\": 0.0006861757124292853, \"text\": \"Schneider\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schneider-Creusot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schneider-Creusot\"}, {\"begin\": 1287, \"end\": 1299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9985112095972136, \"rank\": 0.0014910099822959529, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Related  Even the Catholic Church in Franceslammedthat particular part of the opening ceremony as a \\\"derision and mockery of Christianity.\\\"\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1349, \"end\": 1364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999997626219, \"rank\": 2.2674277954477776e-10, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1456, \"end\": 1468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9985112095972136, \"rank\": 0.0014910099822959529, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So why is the religious right up in arms?\", \"from\": 1472, \"to\": 1513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Salon breaks it down:  The controversial tableau features numerous drag performers, dancers and actors lined up against a long table.\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At some point, the table turns into a catwalk for models to show off gender-fluid fashions.\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1739, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Later, French actor and singer Philippe Katerine - painted entirely blue and wearing nothing but flowers - descends onto the table from a giant food platter.\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1747, \"end\": 1753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9997779783834212, \"rank\": 0.00014483596227688183, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The silver dome is raised to display him in all his glory as the Greek god Dionysus, reclining among fruits and flowers.\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 2018, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1963, \"end\": 1968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9982420756945265, \"rank\": 0.0016523605781698432, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1326237716773865e-27, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The official Olympic X accounttweeteda photo of Katerine, saying, \\\"The interpretation of the Greek God Dionysus makes us aware of the absurdity of violence between human beings.\\\"\", \"from\": 2020, \"to\": 2198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2113, \"end\": 2118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9982420756945265, \"rank\": 0.0016523605781698432, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 2123, \"end\": 2131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1326237716773865e-27, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The interpretation of the Greek God Dionysus makes us aware of the absurdity of violence between human beings.#Paris2024#OpeningCeremonypic.twitter.com/FBlQNNUmvV  - The Olympic Games (@Olympics)July 26, 2024    However, the campy French performance paying homage to Greek mythology and the Olympics' Greek origins was met with swift pushback for those who\\u00a0instead viewed it as a modern-day reenactment of Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper.\\\"\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2226, \"end\": 2231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9982420756945265, \"rank\": 0.0016523605781698432, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 2236, \"end\": 2244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1326237716773865e-27, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 2431, \"end\": 2437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9997779783834212, \"rank\": 0.00014483596227688183, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2467, \"end\": 2482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9999999997603481, \"rank\": 2.3944501133980485e-10, \"text\": \"Greek mythology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 2501, \"end\": 2506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9982420756945265, \"rank\": 0.0016523605781698432, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 2606, \"end\": 2623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1362412658911769e-35, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The painting itself refers to the final meal that Jesus Christ and his 12 apostles had before he was\\u00a0crucified, and is popular in Christian art.\", \"from\": 2645, \"to\": 2789, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2695, \"end\": 2707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.991293468921413e-13, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 2775, \"end\": 2788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_art\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian art\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_art\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_art\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Critics from the Catholic Church in France to American politicians have called the tableau \\\"satanic,\\\" and according to Speaker Johnson, the performance was a \\\"mockery of the Last Supper\\\" and an \\\"insult to Christian people around the world.\\\"\", \"from\": 2791, \"to\": 3031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2808, \"end\": 2823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999997626219, \"rank\": 2.2674277954477776e-10, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 2827, \"end\": 2833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997137421310541, \"rank\": 0.0002842203827754833, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2837, \"end\": 2845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999997753548, \"rank\": 1.7822930063124125e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2918, \"end\": 2925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.586003047834001e-13, \"text\": \"Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\"}, {\"begin\": 2996, \"end\": 3005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9859751275191647, \"rank\": 0.014224367420219246, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Any comment?pic.twitter.com/NJEHaQkgzy  - Dianora Guicciardini (@dianoraguicc)July 26, 2024    This wasn't the only vignette that was met with criticism.\", \"from\": 3033, \"to\": 3186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3083, \"end\": 3095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francesco_Guicciardini\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8229187750998223e-13, \"text\": \"Guicciardini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francesco_Guicciardini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francesco_Guicciardini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another part of the ceremony featured aheadless Marie Antoinettefigure at the Conciergerie - the prison where she was held before being beheaded during the French Revolution - and was also called \\\"satanic\\\" by critics online.\", \"from\": 3187, \"to\": 3411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3265, \"end\": 3277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.756304547380404e-40, \"text\": \"Conciergerie\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Soon after the accusations of religious denigration, in a statement, the opening ceremony producerssaid,\\u00a0\\\"For the 'Festivities' segment, Thomas Jolly took inspiration from Leonardo da Vinci's famous painting to create the setting.\", \"from\": 3413, \"to\": 3643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3550, \"end\": 3556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9939159998373861, \"rank\": 0.006096779232075484, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 3585, \"end\": 3602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1362412658911769e-35, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clearly, there was never an intention to show disrespect towards any religious group or belief \\u2026 [Jolly] is not the first artist to make a reference to what is a world-famous work of art.\", \"from\": 3644, \"to\": 3831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From Andy Warhol to 'The Simpsons,' many have done it before him.\\\"\", \"from\": 3832, \"to\": 3898, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3837, \"end\": 3848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Warhol\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2811649965518496e-53, \"text\": \"Andy Warhol\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Warhol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Warhol\"}, {\"begin\": 3853, \"end\": 3865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Simpsons\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.547640020673397e-16, \"text\": \"The Simpsons\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Simpsons\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Simpsons\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, in a conflicting statement, JollytoldFrench broadcaster BFMTV on Sunday \\\"That wasn't my inspiration and that should be pretty obvious.\", \"from\": 3900, \"to\": 4043, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is Dionysus arriving on a table.\", \"from\": 4045, \"to\": 4084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4055, \"end\": 4063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1326237716773865e-27, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why is he there?\", \"from\": 4085, \"to\": 4101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"First and foremost because he is the god of celebration in Greek mythology, and the tableau is called 'Festivity,'\\\" Jolly elaborated.\", \"from\": 4102, \"to\": 4235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4161, \"end\": 4176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9999999997603481, \"rank\": 2.3944501133980485e-10, \"text\": \"Greek mythology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He is also the god of wine, which is also one of the jewels of France, and the father of S\\u00e9quana, the goddess of the river Seine.\", \"from\": 4236, \"to\": 4366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4300, \"end\": 4306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997137421310541, \"rank\": 0.0002842203827754833, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The idea was to depict a big pagan celebration, linked to the gods of Olympus, and thus the Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 4367, \"to\": 4469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4437, \"end\": 4444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.761880029316068e-14, \"text\": \"Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee also took tosocial mediato address the controversy.\", \"from\": 4471, \"to\": 4558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4475, \"end\": 4506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In the daily press briefing, the Organising Committee said that there was never any intention to show disrespect towards any religious group or belief,\\\" the statement said.\", \"from\": 4560, \"to\": 4733, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC continued, \\\"They reiterated that their intention with the Opening Ceremony was always to celebrate community and tolerance.\", \"from\": 4735, \"to\": 4866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4739, \"end\": 4742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6395832312941665e-23, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 4801, \"end\": 4817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9072515404863978, \"rank\": 0.10153607517410666, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Organising Committee also said that if anyone was offended by certain scenes, this was completely unintentional and they were sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 4867, \"to\": 5004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We need your help to stay independent  Katerine, who performed as the Greek god, Dionysus, was proud of the performance.\", \"from\": 5006, \"to\": 5126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5076, \"end\": 5081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9982420756945265, \"rank\": 0.0016523605781698432, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 5087, \"end\": 5095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1326237716773865e-27, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hesaid, \\\"It's my culture.\", \"from\": 5127, \"to\": 5152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are full of different people and everyone lives their own way and, above all, has the right to do so.\", \"from\": 5153, \"to\": 5257, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I loved doing it.\\\"\", \"from\": 5258, \"to\": 5276, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Barbara Butch, one of the drag queens at the center of the visual, who can be spotted wearing a headpiece,issueda statement condemning the vitriolic response directed towards her for the performance.\", \"from\": 5278, \"to\": 5477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5278, \"end\": 5291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Since the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games, artist, DJ, and activist Barbara Butch has been the target of an extremely violent campaign of cyber-harassment and defamation,\\\" a statement from her attorney said.\", \"from\": 5479, \"to\": 5704, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5565, \"end\": 5578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She has been threatened with death, torture, and rape, and has also been the target of numerous antisemitic, homophobic, sexist, and grossophobic insults.\", \"from\": 5705, \"to\": 5860, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Barbara Butch condemns this vile hatred directed at her, what she represents, and what she stands for.\\\"\", \"from\": 5861, \"to\": 5964, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5861, \"end\": 5874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement concluded, \\\"She is today filing several complaints against these acts, whether committed by French nationals or foreigners, and intends to prosecute anyone who tries to intimidate her in the future.\\\"\", \"from\": 5966, \"to\": 6179, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6072, \"end\": 6078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9997779783834212, \"rank\": 0.00014483596227688183, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more  about this topic  Copyright \\u00a9 2026 Salon.com, LLC.\", \"from\": 6181, \"to\": 6242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6227, \"end\": 6236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\":